1
00:01:02,072 --> 00:01:02,991
Done, done, done!

2
00:01:02,991 --> 00:01:04,492
I'd say you

3
00:01:04,492 --> 00:01:07,023
Head for Dado's; we'll get ready and come.

4
00:01:07,023 --> 00:01:07,631
Okay.

5
00:01:07,631 --> 00:01:08,811
See you.

6
00:01:08,811 --> 00:01:11,021
Bye.

7
00:01:11,736 --> 00:01:12,621
May I go?

8
00:01:12,621 --> 00:01:14,103
Why not? Go.

9
00:01:14,103 --> 00:01:16,151
Listen!

10
00:01:16,151 --> 00:01:16,946
Up there

11
00:01:16,946 --> 00:01:18,217
On the writing table

12
00:01:18,217 --> 00:01:20,542
Is Maheen's diary.

13
00:01:20,542 --> 00:01:21,400
I think

14
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:24,663
She forgot to keep it in the drawer.

15
00:01:24,663 --> 00:01:25,680
Please,

16
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:28,465
Don't read it.

17
00:01:28,465 --> 00:01:30,774
Who knows what it may conceal!

18
00:01:30,774 --> 00:01:31,841
Come on, mate.

19
00:01:31,841 --> 00:01:34,117
I don't read others' diaries.

20
00:01:34,117 --> 00:01:35,310
Well,

21
00:01:35,310 --> 00:01:37,351
May nobody read the diary of one

22
00:01:37,351 --> 00:01:41,992
Who's accused of loving someone else.

23
00:01:41,992 --> 00:01:44,540
And don't even touch

24
00:01:44,540 --> 00:01:47,794
Your enemy's diary!

25
00:01:47,794 --> 00:01:52,830
Otherwise, friendship with her will be impossible.

26
00:01:52,830 --> 00:01:53,673
Alright,

27
00:01:53,673 --> 00:01:54,829
Bye.

28
00:01:54,829 --> 00:01:56,954
Bye.

29
00:02:00,642 --> 00:02:02,630
Have to dash!

30
00:02:04,747 --> 00:02:07,262
It's a love marriage,

31
00:02:07,262 --> 00:02:09,511
Innit?

32
00:02:09,511 --> 00:02:10,902
What does it look like?

33
00:02:10,902 --> 00:02:14,809
It's 100% a love marriage.

34
00:02:14,809 --> 00:02:16,216
Someone must've told you.

35
00:02:16,216 --> 00:02:17,153
No?

36
00:02:17,153 --> 00:02:18,230
Not at all.

37
00:02:18,230 --> 00:02:21,811
Nobody told me.

38
00:02:21,811 --> 00:02:24,884
How do you know, then?

39
00:02:24,884 --> 00:02:26,341
It's etched

40
00:02:26,341 --> 00:02:28,480
On the girl's face.

41
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:30,965
If you ask her to close her eyes,

42
00:02:30,965 --> 00:02:34,565
She opens them repeatedly.

43
00:02:34,565 --> 00:02:36,028
Why?

44
00:02:36,028 --> 00:02:38,371
She doesn't quite believe it, I think,

45
00:02:38,371 --> 00:02:40,924
And she tries to see it again

46
00:02:40,924 --> 00:02:43,527
To believe it.

47
00:02:43,527 --> 00:02:45,282
Even if you tell her a good joke,

48
00:02:45,282 --> 00:02:47,734
She says, 'Hmm... What was that'?

49
00:02:47,734 --> 00:02:49,413
And she's chuffed to have someone

50
00:02:49,413 --> 00:02:53,083
Who'd get her decked up quickly!

51
00:02:53,083 --> 00:02:54,933
And she starts laughing

52
00:02:54,933 --> 00:02:58,433
Like you are every now and then.

53
00:03:00,486 --> 00:03:04,640
You're almost ready.

54
00:03:04,640 --> 00:03:08,969
In just a moment, now, you...

55
00:03:17,862 --> 00:03:19,977
Here, Nano.

56
00:03:19,977 --> 00:03:22,421
The bride's jewellery.

57
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:33,060
Come here, let me kiss your forehead.

58
00:03:37,611 --> 00:03:39,811
May you live long.

59
00:04:02,389 --> 00:04:03,670
On the writing table

60
00:04:03,670 --> 00:04:05,981
Is Maheen's diary.

61
00:04:05,981 --> 00:04:06,853
I think

62
00:04:06,853 --> 00:04:10,166
She forgot to keep it in the drawer.

63
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:11,098
Please,

64
00:04:11,098 --> 00:04:13,105
Don't read it.

65
00:04:13,105 --> 00:04:16,138
Who knows what it may conceal!

66
00:04:16,138 --> 00:04:17,311
Well,

67
00:04:17,311 --> 00:04:19,418
May nobody read the diary of one

68
00:04:19,418 --> 00:04:26,232
Who's accused of loving someone else.

69
00:04:26,232 --> 00:04:28,708
And don't even touch

70
00:04:28,708 --> 00:04:32,912
Your enemy's diary!

71
00:05:00,616 --> 00:05:03,566
Is it that Gulrez loves me,

72
00:05:03,566 --> 00:05:06,916
Or that he worships me?

73
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:09,476
I start to question myself

74
00:05:09,476 --> 00:05:13,386
If I'd ever be able to take such love.

75
00:05:13,386 --> 00:05:14,996
Please, Gulrez,

76
00:05:14,996 --> 00:05:17,315
Keep on loving me.

77
00:05:17,315 --> 00:05:22,159
In time, I'll learn to take it.

78
00:05:22,159 --> 00:05:24,735
Neelam told me today

79
00:05:24,735 --> 00:05:27,735
That you'd purchased a bindiya [ornament] for me.

80
00:05:27,735 --> 00:05:31,196
I smiled coyly to myself for long.

81
00:05:31,196 --> 00:05:32,909
What are you made of, Gulrez,

82
00:05:32,909 --> 00:05:37,079
Remembering every single detail like you do?

83
00:05:37,079 --> 00:05:39,282
That muppet, that Londoner tramp,

84
00:05:39,282 --> 00:05:41,143
He's landed in Karachi.

85
00:05:41,143 --> 00:05:46,813
Looking at him, I'm reminded of his slap.

86
00:05:46,813 --> 00:05:49,457
There is but one thing my heart longs for,

87
00:05:49,457 --> 00:05:54,423
And that is the day when I'd get even with him.

88
00:06:09,653 --> 00:06:19,155
<i>In the tale of love where do these turns come from</i>

89
00:06:19,155 --> 00:06:28,461
<i>That those we hold dear to us are the ones who break our heart</i>

90
00:06:28,461 --> 00:06:39,930
<i>That those we hold dear to us are the ones who break our heart</i>

91
00:07:12,732 --> 00:07:15,514
Why are you smiling?

92
00:07:15,514 --> 00:07:17,591
These looks could kill

93
00:07:17,591 --> 00:07:20,757
Anybody unfortunate enough to meet your gaze!

94
00:07:20,757 --> 00:07:24,770
You look so sweet!

95
00:07:24,770 --> 00:07:27,717
My gaze would only meet his today.

96
00:07:27,717 --> 00:07:31,686
It'll be like an offering unto him.

97
00:07:53,644 --> 00:07:55,298
Dastoor!

98
00:07:55,298 --> 00:07:57,366
Come here.

99
00:08:02,716 --> 00:08:04,668
Yes, Ammi Begum?

100
00:08:04,668 --> 00:08:10,558
Molvi Sahab is going over the top of the dishes, gorbing everything he can.

101
00:08:10,558 --> 00:08:12,208
Call the nincompoop,

102
00:08:12,208 --> 00:08:13,651
Ask him to come here with the procession.

103
00:08:13,651 --> 00:08:15,401
Alright.

104
00:08:15,401 --> 00:08:17,933
Listen,
-Yes?

105
00:08:17,933 --> 00:08:21,061
Just say what I've told you, and not a word beyond it. Go, now.

106
00:08:21,061 --> 00:08:23,433
Alright, Ammi Begum.

107
00:08:24,421 --> 00:08:26,234
There, now!

108
00:08:26,234 --> 00:08:28,129
Would you look at this wee lassie!

109
00:08:28,129 --> 00:08:30,188
The filly's showing up now!

110
00:08:30,188 --> 00:08:32,157
Go!

111
00:08:38,117 --> 00:08:40,351
Why are you quiet?

112
00:08:40,351 --> 00:08:42,540
You're quiet.

113
00:08:42,540 --> 00:08:45,320
That's why.

114
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:47,162
I don't know why, Ali,

115
00:08:47,162 --> 00:08:48,975
But my heart grows restless.

116
00:08:48,975 --> 00:08:50,463
Doesn't it?

117
00:08:50,463 --> 00:08:52,325
What do you mean?

118
00:08:52,325 --> 00:08:55,694
My heart grows restless too.

119
00:08:55,694 --> 00:08:57,648
Would you like some water?

120
00:08:57,648 --> 00:08:59,883
Yes.

121
00:08:59,883 --> 00:09:02,681
I'll get some.

122
00:09:27,446 --> 00:09:28,842
Splendid!

123
00:09:28,842 --> 00:09:32,645
Just as the Lord has willed!

124
00:09:34,255 --> 00:09:35,458
Come on.

125
00:09:35,458 --> 00:09:38,038
Don't tarry too much.

126
00:09:38,038 --> 00:09:41,089
As if I have to deck up like a bride, mate!

127
00:09:41,089 --> 00:09:42,301
Just give me 15 minutes,

128
00:09:42,301 --> 00:09:45,131
And I'll be ready.

129
00:09:45,534 --> 00:09:46,636
Let's see...

130
00:09:46,636 --> 00:09:48,673
Make it quick.

131
00:09:57,729 --> 00:09:59,454
It'll take a while, Uncle,

132
00:09:59,454 --> 00:10:01,032
He's dressing up like the groom.

133
00:10:01,032 --> 00:10:03,746
He'll make haste only if you ask him to,

134
00:10:03,746 --> 00:10:08,182
Molvi Sahab over here is going over the top of the dishes, gorbing everything he can.

135
00:10:08,182 --> 00:10:08,777
Sir,

136
00:10:08,777 --> 00:10:10,153
Where's the loo?

137
00:10:10,153 --> 00:10:11,948
This way.

138
00:10:13,098 --> 00:10:14,826
What's there this way, Uncle?

139
00:10:14,826 --> 00:10:17,375
I'm not saying it to you, mate!

140
00:10:17,375 --> 00:10:21,671
Go, Molvi Sahab, the loo's this way.

141
00:10:30,109 --> 00:10:32,170
Waqar!

142
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:35,360
This phone is switched off.

143
00:11:42,370 --> 00:11:44,497
Waqar, please answer me.

144
00:11:44,497 --> 00:11:48,205
Your phone's switched off too!

145
00:11:48,205 --> 00:11:52,205
Waqar, everyone's waiting over there!

146
00:11:54,986 --> 00:11:57,157
Waqar!

147
00:11:58,130 --> 00:12:00,510
Waqar!

148
00:12:05,694 --> 00:12:07,850
Waqar!

149
00:12:13,940 --> 00:12:16,350
Waqar?

150
00:12:43,659 --> 00:12:45,876
Dear Maheen,

151
00:12:45,876 --> 00:12:48,453
It has been a pleasure

152
00:12:48,453 --> 00:12:51,241
That this chapter of our love began,

153
00:12:51,241 --> 00:12:53,374
And we fell in love;

154
00:12:53,374 --> 00:12:56,501
Such love that you agreed to marry me.

155
00:12:56,501 --> 00:12:57,922
Splendid.

156
00:12:57,922 --> 00:13:04,015
Does one wager oneself in one's quest for revenge?

157
00:13:04,015 --> 00:13:07,247
I could've taken two slaps from you had you just said it;

158
00:13:07,247 --> 00:13:11,851
Why did you have to play this elaborate game just to avenge one slap?

159
00:13:11,851 --> 00:13:16,068
Do you have any idea how many people here love you?

160
00:13:16,068 --> 00:13:20,847
There are many besides Gulrez who adore you with all their lives.

161
00:13:20,847 --> 00:13:23,399
Take Ammi Begum, for instance,

162
00:13:23,399 --> 00:13:28,039
She'd kick her sense of justice away when it'd come to you.

163
00:13:28,039 --> 00:13:29,612
Aunt Suraiyya,

164
00:13:29,612 --> 00:13:31,112
Your mother,

165
00:13:31,112 --> 00:13:33,720
Do you have any idea how many woes she's gone through?

166
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:35,725
And your sister Fajr,

167
00:13:35,725 --> 00:13:41,361
She always kept guessing you'd fallen for me!

168
00:13:41,361 --> 00:13:43,267
You silly girl,

169
00:13:43,267 --> 00:13:48,524
At least you could've thought of Gulrez, if none of them.

170
00:13:48,524 --> 00:13:51,034
He kept writhing in love like an animal to be sacrificed,

171
00:13:51,034 --> 00:13:55,160
And kept on doing what you wanted him to.

172
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:56,681
Honestly,

173
00:13:56,681 --> 00:13:58,907
Is he in on this one?

174
00:13:58,907 --> 00:14:01,819
He doesn't seem the type, though.

175
00:14:01,819 --> 00:14:03,938
He's very simple.

176
00:14:03,938 --> 00:14:06,116
He endures sorrow,

177
00:14:06,116 --> 00:14:07,690
But never gives one any.

178
00:14:07,690 --> 00:14:12,329
I thought for long before I threw away the sherwani about what it was --

179
00:14:12,329 --> 00:14:14,878
What were you up to?

180
00:14:14,878 --> 00:14:16,470
At first, it occurred to me

181
00:14:16,470 --> 00:14:18,112
That I should let the vaudeville commence,

182
00:14:18,112 --> 00:14:20,365
But then thought

183
00:14:20,365 --> 00:14:26,332
That if, amidst this vaudeville, we got espoused, your face would be smirched by my name.

184
00:14:26,332 --> 00:14:28,862
Gulrez has done me so many favours

185
00:14:28,862 --> 00:14:33,582
That I find it improper that he should get to wear what I shall take off.

186
00:14:33,582 --> 00:14:36,350
I'm leaving.

187
00:14:36,350 --> 00:14:38,257
I won't be coming back.

188
00:14:38,257 --> 00:14:40,000
And listen,

189
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:43,522
Never before had I wished that you should taste defeat by my hand,

190
00:14:43,522 --> 00:14:47,133
But my heart says that I should leave you bitterly defeated today,

191
00:14:47,133 --> 00:14:51,350
And show you, Maheen, that to triumph in the name of love,

192
00:14:51,350 --> 00:14:54,126
One has to yield.

193
00:14:54,126 --> 00:14:56,717
I depart a victor,

194
00:14:56,717 --> 00:14:58,803
And I say this as I leave,

195
00:14:58,803 --> 00:15:00,836
'Bless you'

196
00:15:00,836 --> 00:15:04,846
'With this closing checkmate'.

197
00:15:19,987 --> 00:15:32,502
<i>What good is writhing and smouldering in your remembrance</i>

198
00:15:35,517 --> 00:15:38,121
After eight long years, I'm hearing

199
00:15:38,121 --> 00:15:43,084
The rathe shuffling of your footsteps...

200
00:15:41,253 --> 00:15:57,971
<i>Love's testimony is not to be asked of it</i>

201
00:15:57,971 --> 00:16:11,676
<i>It pulls out tears and drops them from the eyes</i>

202
00:15:54,198 --> 00:16:00,306
Just like this, you used to come eagerly, hying --

203
00:16:02,611 --> 00:16:10,139
As if you'd trample everyone under your feet...

204
00:16:11,676 --> 00:16:21,138
<i>In the tale of love where do these turns come from</i>

205
00:16:21,138 --> 00:16:30,355
<i>That those we hold dear to us are the ones who break our heart</i>

